Inside neutron stars we can find the weird

vocabulary.definition: having the closely compacted substance or parts
vocabulary.example: Neutron stars are the densest things that are not black holes.
Strange matter is a bizarre thing that bends the rules of the universe.
Quarks are confined particles that try to pull themselves back together.

vocabulary.definition: remains or impressions of a prehistoric organism preserved in petrified form or as a mold or cast in rock
vocabulary.example: Neutron star cores are like fossils that can provide insights into the universe's past.
Strange matter is considered indestructible, more stable than any other matter in the universe.

vocabulary.definition: the forming of a theory or conjecture without firm evidence
vocabulary.example: The idea that strangelets might be dark matter is pure speculation at this point.
